headlines.description: — The Atlanta Hawks finally rediscovered the late-game composure that helped take them to the Eastern Conference finals last season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young scores 27 points, Hawks hold off Clippers 112-106

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 31 points and eight rebounds, Jaylen Brown added 22 points and eight rebounds and the Boston Celtics beat the Detroit Pistons 114-103 on Friday night for their fifth victory in a row.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayson Tatum scores 31 points, Celtics beat Pistons 114-103

headlines.description: — The Miami Heat are campaigning for Bam Adebayo to get defensive player of the year consideration.
headlines.shortLinkText: Adebayo scores 30 points, Heat pull away to beat Cavs

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 30 points, Dwight Powell tied a career high with 26 and the Dallas Mavericks built a big lead and coasted to 113-100 victory over the Houston Rockets on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic has 30 points, Mavericks beat Rockets 113-100

events.name: New York Knicks at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Ja Morant keyed a fourth-quarter rally by scoring 15 of his 37 points in the period to lead the Memphis Grizzlies to a 118-114 victory over the New York Knicks on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant scores 37 points, Grizzlies turn back Knicks 118-114

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Miles Bridges had 27 points and nine assists, Terry Rozier highlighted his 27-point performance with seven 3-pointers and the Charlotte Hornets put on a shooting exhibition to beat the undermanned New Orleans Pelicans 142-120 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridges, Rozier help Hornets shoot past Pelicans, 142-120

events.name: Utah Jazz at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Gregg Popovich's name is on top of the NBA regular-season victory list. He thinks of it more as a group accomplishment.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs' Gregg Popovich becomes NBA regular-season wins leader

headlines.description: — The Toronto Raptors missed Fred VanVleet for five games with a knee injury. Now that the All-Star is back, Gary Trent Jr. and the rest of the Raptors feel anything is possible.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gary Trent Jr. scores 42 points, Raptors hold off Suns

events.name: Washington Wizards at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James continues to put on age-defying performances.
headlines.shortLinkText: James scores 50, rallies Lakers past Wizards for 122-109 win
